                     <interp inst="t18200412-120-defend1124" type="age" value="17"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t18200412-120-off691" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18200412-120-off691" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200412-120-off691" type="offenceSubcategory" value="pocketpicking"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18200412-120-cd692" type="crimeDate">7th of April</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200412-120-off691 t18200412-120-cd692"></join>, one seal, value 20 s.; two rings, value 2 s., and one key, value 6 d., the goods of 
                     <persName id="t18200412-120-victim1125" type="victimName">
                        John 
                        Watkins
                     <interp inst="t18200412-120-victim1125" type="surname" value="Watkins"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18200412-120-victim1125" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18200412-120-victim1125" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200412-120-off691 t18200412-120-victim1125"></join>
                     </persName>
                  , from his person
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200412-120-person1126">
                  JOHN 
                  WATKINS
               <interp inst="t18200412-120-person1126" type="surname" value="WATKINS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200412-120-person1126" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200412-120-person1126" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in Crown-street, Finsbury-square, and am a <rs id="t18200412-120-viclabel693" type="occupation">corn and nail operator</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200412-120-victim1125 t18200412-120-viclabel693"></join>. On the 7th of April, I was in the <placeName id="t18200412-120-crimeloc694">Strand</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18200412-120-crimeloc694" type="placeName" value="Strand"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18200412-120-crimeloc694" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200412-120-off691 t18200412-120-crimeloc694"></join>, about eight o'clock, and met the prisoner near St. Martin's-lane. He made a snatch at my watch-chain - the chain gave way, and two rings went with the seal; he ran off. I pursued him, calling Stop thief! he cried out also, and ran through the courts towards Chandos-street; I was close behind him, but not near enough to lay hold of him. He was met by Greve, who stopped him. I found my key on the ground, but not the seal.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182004120049"></xptr>
            
                  <persName id="t18200412-120-person1127">
                  HENRY 
                  GREVE
               <interp inst="t18200412-120-person1127" type="surname" value="GREVE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200412-120-person1127" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200412-120-person1127" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I heard the cry, and stopped the prisoner, who was also crying Stop thief! - we both fell together; the prosecutor charged the prisoner with robbing him. I took him to Bow-street, and picked up the key.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I heard the cry, and ran with the rest, saw somebody run into the public-house, and ran in after him.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18200412-120-verdict695" type="verdictDescription">
